cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the security risks and game-theoretic models of arbitrage bots in decentralized exchanges, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also analyzes the profit-making strategies of these bots, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the systemic risks posed by transaction-ordering dependencies in smart contracts, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
